  <prompt>
Close UAT items 3 + 4 + 6 from the 2026-06-18 widget/app parity audit. Hoist the full Kanban experience (drag-drop + orientation toggle + multi-select + card tools + pin) from the SmartTodo Code Page into the `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` peer package. The widget swaps its R4-101 grouped lists for the full hoisted Kanban. The app's SmartToDo.tsx swaps import sources to the peer package. Closes the "13-file rich-feature subtree" follow-up deferred from R4-020 + R4-101.
  </prompt>

  <role>
React + Fluent v9 + react-dnd engineer comfortable with peer-package hoists and the existing R4-070 KanbanBoard shared-lib component (which has the orientation prop scaffolding from Wave A).
  </role>

  <goal>
Widget renders the FULL Kanban (not just grouped lists from R4-101): 3 columns (Today/Tomorrow/Future), cards draggable between columns, multi-select via checkboxes, per-card tool icons (Open + Pin + others matching app), orientation toggle (vertical/horizontal). The hoist re-houses ALL Kanban-related code in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` peer package. The Code Page's Kanban consumer becomes a thin call into the peer package. Drag-drop persists column changes via the existing app pattern. Pin state persists via the existing `sprk_todo` Dataverse field. Selection state model is `Set&lt;string&gt;` (multi), not single. Both surfaces share ONE source of truth for Kanban behavior.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="audit-findings">projects/smart-todo-r4/notes/e-widget-app-parity-audit-2026-06-18.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/smart-todo-r4/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="kanban-source-app">src/solutions/SmartTodo/src/components/SmartToDo.tsx</file>
