    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Peer-package hoist precedent" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.SmartTodo.Components (R4-101 hoisted useKanbanColumns)">
        Hoisting useKanbanColumns in R4-101 established the pattern. This task extends it for the full Kanban component tree.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Existing shared-lib Kanban" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/Kanban/KanbanBoard.tsx">
        R4-070 already created a partial Kanban in `@spaarke/ui-components` with orientation prop. Decide: extend that file vs. create a new full Kanban in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components`. Recommended: keep the visual primitive `KanbanBoard` in `@spaarke/ui-components` (generic) but put the SmartTodo-specific Kanban container + drag-drop wiring + pin handler in `@spaarke/smart-todo-components` (domain-specific). Mirrors Calendar pattern: generic primitives in `@spaarke/ui-components`, domain-specific composition in the peer package.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      UAT 2026-06-18 (post-Wave-D-deploy) requested the widget have the SAME interactivity as the app: drag-drop, orientation toggle, multi-select with card tool icons, pin. Wave D shipped grouped LISTS (read-only) per R4-101 scope. This task is the deferred "full Kanban hoist" promised in R4-020 closeout. The hoist also enables a single-source-of-truth model for the Kanban behavior — when the app changes Kanban behavior, the widget gets it for free, and vice versa.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="R4-020" status="must-complete">Peer package exists</dependency>
      <dependency task="R4-099" status="must-complete">Widget chrome consolidation done; selection state model in place to upgrade</dependency>
      <dependency task="R4-101" status="must-complete">useKanbanColumns already hoisted; this task adds the visual/interactive layer on top</dependency>
    </dependencies>
