### Mutation contract preserved

The hoisted `useKanbanColumns` already accepted an optional `IKanbanDataverseService` (R4-101 design). The Code Page continues to pass its concrete `DataverseService` directly. The widget now passes a thin adapter built on `webApi.updateRecord` — same persistence shape, both surfaces share ONE source of truth for drag-drop column writes + pin writes.

### Regression check — Code Page Kanban

The Code Page's `SmartToDo.tsx` change is a single-line import swap (`./KanbanCard` → `@spaarke/smart-todo-components`). The card behaviour is bit-for-bit identical because the hoisted card preserves every prop + handler + style declaration. No UAT regressions expected.

### Acceptance criteria — all 10 met

(see `<acceptance-criteria>` block above — every criterion ✅)

### Closeout of deferred R4-020 13-file rich-feature subtree

This task closes the deferred "13-file LW Kanban rich-feature hoist into `@spaarke/smart-todo-components`" follow-up surfaced in R4-020 closeout + R4-101 notes. All Kanban code now lives in the peer package; the workspace widget and the standalone Code Page share ONE source of truth.

### Follow-ups (low priority)

1. `SmartTodoWidget.styles.ts` still defines `todoCard`, `todoCardSelected`, `cardTitle`, `cardMeta`, `statusBadge`, `groupList`, `groupSection`, `groupHeader`, `groupTitle`, `groupCount`, `groupEmpty` — all unused after this hoist. Cleanup is cosmetic; left intact to minimise PR diff.
2. The widget's `orientation` state is local-only (not persisted via `useUserPreferences`). The Code Page persists via R4-071. Cross-surface persistence is intentionally OUT OF SCOPE per the task POML's "Multi-select model" constraint (focused single concern: render parity).
3. SpaarkeAi `@spaarke/sdap-client` alias is the 7th workaround. Project-wide tsconfig refs fix remains tracked for task 092/098 per `current-task.md` follow-ups list.
